Description:
Classic brick veneer home
Hidden behind a beautiful hedge is this classic three bedroom brick veneer home. It comprises good sized formal lounge with brick fireplace surround and decorative cornice. The separate sun-filled kitchen has been renovated and offers an abundance of bench space and cupboards and overlooks the meals room. All three bedrooms are spacious in size with a central bathroom which offers bath, pedestal basin and separate shower. Located only 450m from the CBD, this home would be a fantastic investment opportunity or would be ideal for someone wanting to get into the market and purchase their first home. At this price bracket, this home is sure to be snapped up quickly, so make an appointment to view today.

Description:
Fantastic Family Home with Pool!
Beautifully presented, this four bedroom family home has so much to offer. The kitchen/meals area includes an induction cook top, self-cleaning oven, dishwasher, plumbing for ice-maker refrigerator, pantry, wine storage shelves, a large breakfast bar and both formal and informal dining. The three living areas (formal lounge, family area plus rumpus room) will ensure everyone has space for their own interests. Four generous bedrooms, main with walk in robe and ensuite. Three way family bathroom with powder/vanity area, shower and bath, and separate toilet. Ducted vacuum, ducted evaporative cooling and ducted, reverse cycle, split system air conditioning. Double garage under roofline with room for two large cars, twin roller doors and an air conditioned, lockable, storage room. Caravan park at the side. Outdoor, entertaining/BBQ area with shade sails. The securely fenced yard contains a sparkling, solar-heated, inground pool, a substantial cubby house, a 3 metre by 3 metre garden shed with a concrete floor and established, low maintenance gardens. Quiet, court location in one of the earlier Murray River Estate sub-divisions.
Vendor is relocating and has priced to sell. Won't last at this price!
